SBIePay 2.0 DC-DR Drill – Delay Update

Dear Sir/Madam,

This is to update you on the DC-to-DR switchover drill carried out today for SBIePay 2.0. The switchover was completed successfully; however, we encountered a delay during execution, and we would like to share the details along with our observations for improvement.

Issue 1: Slow Base Image Pull
During pipeline execution, we observed that the GitLab Runner helper base image took approximately 45-50 seconds to pull from our Artifactory registry before the deployment job could proceed. This added avoidable latency at the start of every job run.

Issue 2: DNS Resolution Failure (gitlab.sbi)
One of the pipeline jobs failed with the error "Could not resolve host: gitlab.sbi" while attempting to fetch the source repository from the DR-side runner. This is a transient DNS resolution issue on the runner/network side. As a result, the job had to be manually re-triggered, and it completed successfully on the second attempt.

Impact
These two issues together contributed to the overall delay in completing the drill within the originally planned time window. The switchover itself was validated successfully once the pipeline completed.

Scope of Improvement
1. Pre-warm/cache the GitLab Runner helper image on DR runners so it does not need to be pulled fresh during time-critical drills.
2. Investigate and stabilize DNS resolution for gitlab.sbi from the DR runner network - likely a resolver/hosts-file or CoreDNS configuration gap specific to the DR side.
3. Add a retry-with-backoff mechanism in the pipeline for transient git-fetch/DNS failures, so jobs self-recover without manual re-triggering.
4. Include a pre-drill runner health check (DNS resolution + registry connectivity) as a checklist item before future DC-DR drills.

We will work with the infra team to address these gaps before the next scheduled drill. Please let us know if you need any further details.

Regards,
DevSecOps Team

